In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2012 as Military Family Month. He acknowledges the sacrifices and contributions made by military families and emphasizes the importance of showing them care and respect. He highlights the work of the Joining Forces initiative, led by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden, in mobilizing Americans to support service members and their families. The initiative has encouraged businesses to hire veterans and military spouses, and it has already surpassed its goal of 100,000 hires. President Obama calls on all Americans to honor military families through private actions and public service. He concludes by reaffirming the commitment to support military families not just during deployments but also after their loved ones return home.